snippet.textDisplay: The reason being is that education institutions have been using Zoom way before Covid19 due to being better at handling video feeds. They mainly uses it for conferences because it could handle a larger volume and has more functionalities for education purposes than Skype or Discord offer like Canvas integration, or break room for discussion, etc. Therefore, when this pandemic hits, it would just be easier for schools to expand their already existed Zoom deal. Instructors are also familiar with the application beforehand, and IT also already knows what technical errors to be expected from Zoom. Nonetheless, instructors could only access Zoom through specific college domain, adding another layer of security protection not just from Zoom. That's why schools use Zoom.
